==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Charnel
<hw>Char"nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>charnel</ets> carnal, fleshly, fr. L. <ets>carnalis</ets>. See
<er>Carnal</er>.]</ety> <def>Containing the bodies of the dead.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Charnel</xex> vaults.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Charnel house</b></col>, <cd>a tomb, vault, cemetery, or
other place where the bones of the dead are deposited; originally, a
place for the bones thrown up when digging new graves in old burial
grounds.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charnel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Charnel
<hw>Char"nel</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A charnel house; a grave; a
cemetery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In their proud <qex>charnel</qex> of Thermopyl⟦ae⟧.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charon</ent>⟦br⟧
